FBIS4-42507 "drweu108_h_94013" FBIS-WEU-94-108 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 GERMANY 3,000 Demonstrate in Northeim Against FAP 3,000 Demonstrate in Northeim Against FAP LD0406172594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1641 GMT 4 Jun 94 LD0406172594 Berlin DDP/ADN German BFN [Excerpts] Northeim (DDP/ADN) -- Approximately 3,000 people attended a demonstration against the right-wing Free German Workers' Party (FAP) in Northeim/Lower Saxony today. Clashes between demonstrators and police, in which several people were injured, occurred late this afternoon at the police cordon outside the home of Thorsten Heise, the chairman of the Lower Saxony and Saxony-Anhalt regional association, who was arrested on Thursday [2 June]. [passage omitted] Twenty-four-year-old Heise has previous convictions and is considered the brains behind many violent actions carried out by right-wing extremists. [passage omitted]
